# Data & network rules

## Resilience

- Use stdlib `logging` (not print) for operational output.
- Set **timeouts** on every HTTP/request call.
- Retry with **exponential backoff** on transient failures.
- **Never let one symbol's failure kill a batch run** — log, skip, continue.

## Timezone

All dates flow through `zoneinfo.ZoneInfo(cfg["timezone"])`. Never use bare `date.today()`.

## yfinance

- Respect `request_sleep_s` between **every** `option_chain()` call, not just per symbol.
- Off-hours chains may have bid/ask of 0 — filters already define `no_quote` FAIL behavior; do not special-case elsewhere.

## ApeWisdom

Field names are unofficial. On first integration, log `results[0].keys()` at DEBUG and map fields in **one place** only (`data/mentions.py`).

## SQLite

Single writer — no threading. Jobs are serialized via systemd timers.
